properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 10 at 11:06AM MST until January 10 at 10:00PM MST by NWS Albuquerque NM
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 45 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Curry County and Roosevelt County.

* WHEN...From 3 PM this afternoon to 10 PM MST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Additionally, difficult driving conditions are possible for
high profile vehicles on east to west roadways.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Light snow may also develop this evening,
particularly across northern Curry County. Thus, patchy areas of
blowing snow may reduce visibility for a short time this
evening.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 10 PM MST THIS EVENING
